Traineeship Description:
This position is part of the HR team that reports to the Deputy Executive Director, Corporate Services &amp; Special Projects. On a day-to-day basis, the Trainee HR Executive will report to and take instructions from the Senior HR Executive. Other than interfacing with company employees, the trainee will also interact with our external vendors.
As an SSA, New Life’s core mission is to serve the community. We place a premium for people who has a high sense of calling and purpose. The organization desires to build a growth culture, one that allows all employee to grow and develop their full potential. In so doing, they will be empowered and competent to serve their customers – whether it is internal or external.

Specific Responsibilities:
Trainee to be involved in:
1. Employee orientation and training logistics and recordkeeping
2. The implementation of the new HR Management System
3. Rolling out of Employee Engagement Surveys
4. Provide direct support to employees as we review our HR services, policies and programs

Technical Skills and Competencies Trainee will learn during SGUnited Traineeship Programme:
1. How to engage employees professionally
2. How to engage with external vendors – HRMS vendor, insurance vendors, etc.
3. Involved in the different phases of implementing a HRMS – design phase, testing phase, and go-live phase
4. Gain experience in the full cycle of an Employee Engagement Survey

Education Qualifications Required for the Traineeship Role
Bachelor Degree

Eligibility Criteria for SGUnited Traineeships:
Singapore Citizen or Permanent Resident; and
a. Graduated or graduating in calendar year 2019 or 2020 from ITEs, polytechnics, universities, or other educational institutions (e.g. private universities and overseas institutions); or
b. Graduated earlier from above institutions and completed National Service in 2019 or 2020.